1
00:00:06,940 --> 00:00:08,570
This neighborhood is filled with cram schools.

2
00:00:08,570 --> 00:00:10,970
- Right, it's known for them. - Yes. It's filled with them.

3
00:00:11,340 --> 00:00:12,580
Everyone goes to cram schools here.

4
00:00:13,610 --> 00:00:15,310
Goodness, we're in Daechi-dong.

5
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:18,380
(The two MCs are at a restaurant for a change.)

6
00:00:18,380 --> 00:00:19,880
We're starting off today in an unusual way.

7
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:21,920
- We're at a Chinese restaurant. - Right.

8
00:00:22,220 --> 00:00:24,390
- We're having lunch first today. - Right.

9
00:00:24,550 --> 00:00:26,290
We're at a regular restaurant...

10
00:00:26,390 --> 00:00:28,290
- of today's Whenever Friends. - Really?

11
00:00:28,860 --> 00:00:32,360
I guess the Whenever Guests are free in the afternoon.

12
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:33,760
- I see. - Right.

13
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,000
- First of all... - The Whenever Friends must have...

14
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,170
- ties to Daechi-dong. - Right.

15
00:00:37,170 --> 00:00:39,340
If the Whenever Friends have ties to Daechi-dong,

16
00:00:39,340 --> 00:00:40,870
does it mean they were raised in Daechi?

17
00:00:41,470 --> 00:00:42,610
Who are they?

18
00:00:42,710 --> 00:00:43,870
Do you not know who they are?

19
00:00:43,870 --> 00:00:45,210
I didn't get any information.

20
00:00:45,210 --> 00:00:46,680
The staff didn't contact me about them.

21
00:00:46,810 --> 00:00:49,210
- I bet they're from your scene. - Right.

22
00:00:49,210 --> 00:00:51,210
But there are so many actors and actresses.

23
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:52,550
(Trailing off)

24
00:00:52,550 --> 00:00:54,180
I don't know if this is a disappointment or not.

25
00:00:54,180 --> 00:00:56,190
Not that many people from my scene were raised in Daechi.

26
00:00:57,590 --> 00:00:58,860
I mean, they were all young once.

27
00:00:58,860 --> 00:01:00,960
But they didn't grow up around here.

28
00:01:01,790 --> 00:01:02,930
Wait. They're coming.

29
00:01:03,030 --> 00:01:04,060
They're so tall.

30
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:05,430
- Who are they? - Wait.

31
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,100
(Chuckling, sighing)

32
00:01:08,260 --> 00:01:09,630
Let's do a good job with the games.

33
00:01:09,630 --> 00:01:11,100
I think it's that way. Here.

34
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,200
Let's go.

35
00:01:12,770 --> 00:01:13,770
Is this the place?

36
00:01:13,770 --> 00:01:15,170
(Two men with a serious vibe)

37
00:01:15,170 --> 00:01:16,170
Let's do the game with confidence.

38
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,080
I've been coming here for a decade.

39
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:20,110
For a decade?

40
00:01:20,110 --> 00:01:21,580
Their food is much better...

41
00:01:21,580 --> 00:01:23,480
at the restaurant than when delivered.

42
00:01:24,150 --> 00:01:27,180
(The two of them share secret information.)

43
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:30,420
Hello.

44
00:01:30,820 --> 00:01:31,920
- Hello. - Gosh.

45
00:01:32,090 --> 00:01:33,560
It's Sung Woong.

46
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,360
- What? Sung Woong. - Park Sung Woong.

47
00:01:35,690 --> 00:01:36,890
- Seriously. - Who's the other guy?

48
00:01:36,890 --> 00:01:38,030
It's Sung Woong. And who's that?

49
00:01:38,190 --> 00:01:40,630
My gosh, Sung Woong. Hello.

50
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:43,900
(It's the perfect weather to do missions.)

51
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:46,140
(The iconic figure of film noir)

52
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,970
(Even when he's serving justice, the genre turns into film noir.)

53
00:01:49,370 --> 00:01:50,540
(Even his yearning turns into film noir.)

54
00:01:51,170 --> 00:01:52,980
(His concern for the meal turns into film noir.)

55
00:01:53,310 --> 00:01:55,210
(His tears feel like film noir too.)

56
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:58,450
(A man embodying film noir)

57
00:01:58,450 --> 00:01:59,680
(Actor Park Sung Woong)

58
00:02:00,380 --> 00:02:02,990
(The best man in suits)

59
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:04,890
(He's as smart as he is handsome.)

60
00:02:04,890 --> 00:02:06,420
(The SNU graduate and the original dream son)

61
00:02:06,490 --> 00:02:09,590
(He's thriving in dramas, movies, and even plays.)

62
00:02:09,590 --> 00:02:11,060
(Actor Lee Sang Yun)

63
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:13,400
- Hello. - Yes, you're from here!

64
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:16,070
I'm not, actually. But I'm raising my kids here.

65
00:02:16,070 --> 00:02:17,330
(Sung Woong and Jae Suk are the same age.)

66
00:02:17,330 --> 00:02:18,770
- Have you been well? - Hello.

67
00:02:19,370 --> 00:02:21,040
You grew up here, didn't you?

68
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,310
- Hello. - Hello.

69
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:24,370
- Is this your regular spot? - Yes, it is.

70
00:02:25,910 --> 00:02:27,540
- Nice to meet you. - Nice to meet you.

71
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:29,210
- Yes. - I live in the apartment...

72
00:02:29,210 --> 00:02:30,750
right across from this restaurant.

73
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:32,650
- You live around here? - Yes.

74
00:02:32,780 --> 00:02:34,120
- Please take the inner seat. - I see.

75
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,250
So you two are joining us today.

76
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:38,020
- It's been a while. You know? - Gosh.

77
00:02:38,620 --> 00:02:40,290
- It's been a while. - Yes, it's been a while.

78
00:02:40,290 --> 00:02:41,990
When I saw him coming in,

79
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:44,590
- I wondered if he grew up here. - Right.

80
00:02:44,590 --> 00:02:45,860
He got good grades, you know?

81
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:46,960
- Right. - Yes.

82
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:49,600
- I don't have any ties here. - Where did you grow up?

83
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,670
I grew up in Yeouido.

84
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:52,540
- Yeouido? - Yes.

85
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,070
- Do you not know each other? - No.

86
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:57,540
No. And he's 2 or 3 years older than me.

87
00:02:57,540 --> 00:03:00,610
Did you two film a movie or a drama together?

88
00:03:01,140 --> 00:03:02,280
We filmed a movie a long time ago...

89
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:04,380
- called "Okay! Madam." - Right.

90
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:06,550
That's when I got to know him for the first time.

91
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:09,390
He's such a good guy. He's sweet and kind. So I adore him.

92
00:03:09,390 --> 00:03:11,090
- Really? - I see.

93
00:03:11,090 --> 00:03:12,220
So it doesn't sound like you're here...

94
00:03:12,220 --> 00:03:13,960
- to promote something. - No, we're not here for that.

95
00:03:14,090 --> 00:03:15,990
- We're just... - I hear you like watching our show.

96
00:03:15,990 --> 00:03:17,130
We're just real friends.

97
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:19,600
- Really? - It's the same character.

98
00:03:19,830 --> 00:03:22,370
(At that moment, all of a sudden...)

99
00:03:22,370 --> 00:03:23,500
Honey, I'm filming a show.

100
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,670
Okay.

101
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,540
- Hello. - She's your junior.

102
00:03:28,540 --> 00:03:29,640
- Right. - Yes.

103
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:30,740
We went to the same university.

104
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:33,780
The genre suddenly turned into film noir with Sung Woong.

105
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:34,980
No. Lately...

106
00:03:35,910 --> 00:03:37,110
- Go on. - Did you see the look on his face?

107
00:03:37,110 --> 00:03:38,780
I didn't kill anyone last year.

108
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:39,980
(I didn't kill anyone last year.)

109
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,650
- I'm serious. - Really?

110
00:03:42,020 --> 00:03:43,250
- Right. Last year... - You've gone straight now.

111
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:44,890
Yes. I'm playing a character...

112
00:03:44,890 --> 00:03:46,490
who moved back to the countryside to be a farmer.

113
00:03:46,490 --> 00:03:47,690
(He's settling his bad karma with the character.)

114
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:48,990
- A farmer? - Yes.

115
00:03:49,130 --> 00:03:51,730
Are you actually interested in moving back to be a farmer?

116
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:53,860
- I'm not. - I see.

117
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,230
- I bet Jae Suk has zero interest. - None.

118
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:59,640
- What about you? - I like the idea, but I hate bugs.

119
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:00,670
Right!

120
00:04:01,340 --> 00:04:02,940
- You hate bugs. - I do.

121
00:04:02,940 --> 00:04:04,540
- I hate them too. - Same here.

122
00:04:04,810 --> 00:04:06,680
- Like mosquitoes and mayflies. - Wait.

123
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:08,080
- No? - What is it?

124
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,580
- Nothing. - Tell me. What is it?

125
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:12,450
But you're nicknamed after one of them.

126
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:15,280
Are you serious?

127
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,720
Sang Yun, we haven't met in a while.

128
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:18,820
(The former grasshopper is annoyed.)

129
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:20,920
We haven't met in a few years. What an awful thing to say to me.

130
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:21,990
I'm sorry.

131
00:04:21,990 --> 00:04:24,030
Kyung Nam was like that last week.

132
00:04:24,030 --> 00:04:25,660
(Last week, Kyung Nam annoyed Jae Suk.)

133
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:26,830
What should we order?

134
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,330
- Is this your regular restaurant? - Yes.

135
00:04:29,830 --> 00:04:31,070
- Sung Woong comes here often. - Really?

136
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:32,640
I've been coming here for a decade.

137
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:34,570
This is an old restaurant.

138
00:04:34,570 --> 00:04:36,210
I think it's been around for 20 years.

139
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:38,240
- What's good here? - I bet it's all tasty here.

140
00:04:38,740 --> 00:04:40,240
There's a local dish...

141
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,150
- from my hometown. - What is it?

142
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,010
It's called uljjajang.

143
00:04:44,550 --> 00:04:46,150
- Ulmyeon. - Uljjajang?

144
00:04:46,150 --> 00:04:48,350
- I've never heard of it. - It's a mix of ulmyeon and jjajng.

145
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:50,120
You can't find it in Seoul.

146
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:52,190
- So it's ulmyeon... - So...

147
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:55,060
I made the dish here. It tastes exactly the same.

148
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:57,430
- How? - So you're eating them together?

149
00:04:57,430 --> 00:05:00,000
I pour the jjajang sauce to ulmyeon.

150
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,760
- Okay. - It tastes the same once mixed.

151
00:05:01,860 --> 00:05:03,370
So it's similar to watery jjajang, right?

152
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:05,840
It tastes different from the dish people in Jeolla Province eat.

153
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:09,440
This dish from Chungcheong Province is a bit stickier and thicker.

154
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:11,210
- It tastes different? - Right.

155
00:05:11,340 --> 00:05:13,740
So we have to order two dishes? Ulmyeon and jjajangmyeon?

156
00:05:13,740 --> 00:05:15,510
- Right. There are four of us. - Yes.

157
00:05:15,510 --> 00:05:16,780
We can order two each.

158
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:19,450
I'll mix them together, so you can taste it.

159
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,080
- But I want to eat jjamppong. - Me too.

160
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:24,790
- It's the perfect day for it. - Right.

161
00:05:24,790 --> 00:05:27,220
- The weather is perfect for it. - All right then.

162
00:05:27,220 --> 00:05:29,060
- It's the perfect weather for it. - You can have jjamppong.

163
00:05:29,060 --> 00:05:31,160
- Yes. - But we'll have uljjajang.

164
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:33,130
- So you can try the dish. - Sounds good.

165
00:05:33,130 --> 00:05:35,230
To be honest, I wanted a rice dish.

166
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,170
- Do you want japchae rice? - Then, we won't be able...

167
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:38,940
to try uljjajang.

168
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:42,240
You know what, Sung Woong? Only you should get uljjajang.

169
00:05:42,470 --> 00:05:44,140
Or eat it in your hometown.

170
00:05:44,940 --> 00:05:46,480
No one seems to want uljjajang.

171
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:49,580
- Are you from Seoul? - I'm from Seoul.

172
00:05:49,580 --> 00:05:50,580
(Slapping it down)

173
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:53,050
Come on. What is this, guys?

174
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,850
Let's do this then. I'll cancel my white jjamppong.

175
00:05:56,850 --> 00:05:59,290
- Right. Try uljjajang. - Let's order ulmyeon,

176
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:00,720
- jjajangmyeon... - Great.

177
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,760
We have to order tangsuyuk and yangjangpi.

178
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,960
- Sounds good. - Yes.

179
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,930
- They both sound great. - Yangjangpi.

180
00:06:05,930 --> 00:06:07,630
- And japchae rice. - I'll get japchae rice.

181
00:06:07,830 --> 00:06:09,070
- Ma'am. - Yes.

182
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:12,370
- It's regular jjajangmyeon. - Okay.

183
00:06:12,370 --> 00:06:14,640
- Give me the sauce separately. - Sure.

184
00:06:14,740 --> 00:06:17,470
Gosh, he's showing off that this is his regular restaurant.

185
00:06:17,470 --> 00:06:19,380
(He's excited to be at his regular restaurant.)

186
00:06:19,580 --> 00:06:21,280
- My gosh. Ma'am. - That's the owner.

187
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:23,810
- That was fast. - That was super fast.

188
00:06:23,810 --> 00:06:25,110
- Gosh. - What do you say?

189
00:06:25,110 --> 00:06:26,380
Will we pour the sauce or dip it in the sauce?

190
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:28,320
- Eat however you want. - Right.

191
00:06:28,950 --> 00:06:30,850
- Can I pour it on just half of it? - Go ahead.

192
00:06:31,490 --> 00:06:33,060
(Half poured, half dipped)

193
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:35,060
- Pour it on just half? Okay. - Sounds good.

194
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:36,530
- Gosh. - Oh, my.

195
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:38,190
(Yangjangpi is served right away too.)

196
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:40,430
- We're starting with our lunch. - It's yangjangpi.

197
00:06:40,430 --> 00:06:41,530
(The recommended dishes by the regular customer, Sung Woong)

198
00:06:41,530 --> 00:06:42,670
Should I add all of it?

199
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:44,700
Probably. Yes.

200
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,670
(Drizzling it after getting Sung Woong's permission)

201
00:06:46,670 --> 00:06:48,770
You're checking everything with him today.

202
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,270
(Flinching)

203
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:53,480
I think he has his own way of enjoying the dishes here.

204
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,280
Is that it? Or are you scared of him?

205
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:57,380
- Sung Woong... - He's not scared of me.

206
00:06:57,380 --> 00:06:58,920
only comes across scary in his movies and dramas.

207
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:01,120
- He's a sweet guy in real life. - Right.

208
00:07:01,650 --> 00:07:03,490
- Right. - This is his regular restaurant.

209
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:04,650
I just thought he had his own way...

210
00:07:04,650 --> 00:07:06,820
- of enjoying the dishes. - No.

211
00:07:07,390 --> 00:07:09,690
Sung Woong just has to make sure he gets to eat uljjajang.

212
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:10,830
(He's going all in with uljjajang.)

213
00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:12,800
Right. If we didn't order that...

214
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,260
This is great.

215
00:07:14,930 --> 00:07:17,070
- I should start with this. - Starting with Chinese food...

216
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:18,100
Yes.

217
00:07:18,970 --> 00:07:20,000
(Humming)

218
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:21,800
(Smiling)

219
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,910
- The food here tastes great. - I told you.

220
00:07:24,810 --> 00:07:26,310
Do you come here with your family too?

221
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,480
- Yes. My son likes this restaurant. - Food tastes better at restaurants.

222
00:07:29,810 --> 00:07:31,880
- How old is your son? - He's 17.

223
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:33,880
We've been coming here since he was seven.

224
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:34,880
(He's been coming here with his son for 10 years.)

225
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:37,420
Then does your son have uljjajang here?

226
00:07:38,450 --> 00:07:39,490
He gets dry jjajng.

227
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:43,090
- He just gets whatever he wants. - I guess...

228
00:07:43,490 --> 00:07:45,430
not a lot of people like uljjajang.

229
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,130
Gosh, try it.

230
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:50,370
- Thank you. - Here it is.

231
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:51,900
(Jjajangmyeon is also served.)

232
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:54,770
- A special dish by Sung Woong. - Sung Woong said uljjajang...

233
00:07:56,070 --> 00:07:57,270
Can I get a ladle?

234
00:07:57,270 --> 00:07:58,370
(Sung Woong will make the long-awaited uljjajang.)

235
00:07:58,370 --> 00:07:59,480
I'm curious.

236
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:03,250
(He starts mixing uljjajang.)

237
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:08,120
(He scoops up the broth of ulmyeon and adds the jjajang sauce.)

238
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,950
This dish is from Chungju.

239
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:12,520
You can find uljjajang on the menu.

240
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,090
People from Chungcheong Province...

241
00:08:15,090 --> 00:08:17,690
- must be happy to see it. - You know what? It looks tasty.

242
00:08:17,690 --> 00:08:18,930
- It is. - I mean, ulmyeon...

243
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:20,160
- is already tasty by itself. - Right.

244
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:23,800
Yes. You get that seafood flavor from ulmyeon.

245
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,170
It's got a lot of seafood.

246
00:08:25,170 --> 00:08:27,200
So this is a great hangover dish.

247
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,870
- Right. And... - Yes.

248
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:30,570
Jjamppong is here.

249
00:08:31,470 --> 00:08:32,780
Jjamppong looks great.

250
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:34,180
(Changing the topic of his interest)

251
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:36,080
You know what? Jjamppong looks so good.

252
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:37,880
Of course, it's going to be tasty.

253
00:08:39,980 --> 00:08:41,120
(Feeling rushed for some reason)

254
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,220
I'm curious.

255
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:43,650
What do you think, Sang Yun?

256
00:08:43,650 --> 00:08:45,020
- It looks good. - Right?

257
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,620
That does look good.

258
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:50,590
They couldn't have run this place for over 40 years in this town...

259
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:52,330
- if their food hadn't been good. - Try it, Yeon Seok.

260
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:53,960
Okay. I'm curious.

261
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:56,800
(The youngest has a bite of uljjajang first.)

262
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,930
This is a lot of food.

263
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,510
What do you think?

264
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:06,580
(Nervous)

265
00:09:07,010 --> 00:09:08,140
Do you not like it?

266
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,350
It's good.

267
00:09:11,580 --> 00:09:12,720
It looks good.

268
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:14,280
- It's... - It could be a trendy dish.

269
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:16,320
- It's bound to taste great. - Exactly.

270
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:19,260
Ulmyeon with the jjajang sauce...

271
00:09:19,590 --> 00:09:20,690
- tastes like... - Yes.

272
00:09:20,690 --> 00:09:23,030
- a wetter-version of jjajangmyeon. - It's good.

273
00:09:23,030 --> 00:09:24,390
- I bet. - Yes.

274
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:25,490
(Putting aside jjamppong and trying uljjajang)

275
00:09:29,470 --> 00:09:32,300
- It's not thick. It's moist. - Yes.

276
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,340
(Nodding)

277
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,840
It's a moist version of seafood jjajang.

278
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,270
The jjajang sauce...

279
00:09:38,470 --> 00:09:40,510
- It brings up the flavor. - It brings up the flavor.

280
00:09:41,110 --> 00:09:42,650
(Drinking the broth)

281
00:09:42,710 --> 00:09:43,810
It's getting hot.

282
00:09:44,650 --> 00:09:47,080
Sang Yun, why did you order japchae rice?

283
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:49,950
You're inhaling uljjajang.

284
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:52,590
- Do you want more? - It's great.

285
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,660
(I'd like some more.)

286
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:56,490
(Grinning)

287
00:09:56,490 --> 00:09:57,860
- I feel so proud. - You do?

288
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,500
I was worried when they kept complaining earlier.

289
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,430
Today...

290
00:10:03,430 --> 00:10:05,300
- How do you like uljjajang? - It's good.

291
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:07,500
This is really good.

292
00:10:09,910 --> 00:10:12,270
(He can't conceal his joy.)

293
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:15,040
- I feel so proud. - You feel proud.

294
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:16,380
Let me have my food now.

295
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,380
- Go on and eat. - Okay.

296
00:10:23,050 --> 00:10:24,220
We're having uljjajang today.

297
00:10:24,550 --> 00:10:25,620
It's very good.

298
00:10:26,190 --> 00:10:27,960
- This is so good. - Yes.

299
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:31,030
I always have this dish when I go to my hometown.

300
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:32,030
- At a regular restaurant there. - Yes.

301
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:34,530
Then, when did you move to Seoul from Chungcheong Province?

302
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:36,300
- For college. - For college?

303
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:37,370
Yes.

304
00:10:37,430 --> 00:10:39,570
- Where did you grow up? - Jangwi-dong.

305
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,470
- Jangwi-dong, Seongbuk-gu. - Seongbuk-gu.

306
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,470
- That's close to my hometown. - Right.

307
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,810
But the vibes are very different.

308
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:48,040
The overall vibes...

309
00:10:50,010 --> 00:10:51,850
(He gets insulted while enjoying his food.)

310
00:10:51,850 --> 00:10:53,880
- Listen. - I mean... Yes?

311
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,420
- In what ways are we different? - So...

312
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:56,790
The overall vibes...

313
00:10:56,790 --> 00:10:57,790
(Neighboring towns with different vibes)

314
00:10:57,790 --> 00:10:58,820
are slightly different.

315
00:10:59,420 --> 00:11:02,060
Uljjajang will be called Sung Woong's Jjajang.

316
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:04,890
- That's what he wants. Right? - Well...

317
00:11:05,190 --> 00:11:08,230
Let's call it Park Sung Wool Jjajang.

318
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:11,570
- Not a lot of kids eat ulmyeon. - Ulmyeon?

319
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:12,570
- Yes. - They don't.

320
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:15,240
- The broth is thicker. - Because they shouldn't cry.

321
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,140
(Lips twitching)

322
00:11:18,140 --> 00:11:19,740
Sang Yun makes jokes like this.

323
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,180
I'm used to his jokes.

324
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:24,110
He makes more dad jokes than I do.

325
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:26,350
(The fan of dad jokes)

326
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:28,220
I wanted to make that joke, but I didn't.

327
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,720
- Ulmyeon... - "They can't cry."

328
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,750
- You know what? - "They can't cry."

329
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:32,520
Everyone probably thought of the joke.

330
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,520
Exactly.

331
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:34,920
(And he made the joke.)

332
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:36,560
- I held myself back. - We decided not to.

333
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:37,730
- Really? - Yes.

334
00:11:37,730 --> 00:11:39,260
What's the car Santa Claus hates the most?

335
00:11:39,260 --> 00:11:40,960
(Sung Woong's dad joke)

336
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,060
I knew the answer.

337
00:11:42,060 --> 00:11:43,470
The car Santa Claus hates the most.

338
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:44,870
- The car he hates? - Yes.

339
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:48,340
- The car he hates? - Yes. The car he hates.

340
00:11:48,540 --> 00:11:49,870
(What's the car Santa Claus hates the most?)

341
00:11:49,870 --> 00:11:50,940
The car he hates...

342
00:11:51,310 --> 00:11:52,370
Santa Fe.

343
00:11:54,940 --> 00:11:57,650
(The middle-aged man pulls it off.)

344
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:01,020
You told joke like it was nothing.

345
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,750
- I mean, a dad joke... - Picturing him beating up Santa...

346
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:06,090
- looks pretty scary. - No.

347
00:12:06,090 --> 00:12:07,960
- I wouldn't beat him up. - I know.

348
00:12:07,990 --> 00:12:09,930
- Right. - Santa hates the car, Santa Fe.

349
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:11,860
I didn't know about that one, Santa Fe.

350
00:12:11,860 --> 00:12:13,160
- Really? - It was funny.

351
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,230
(Feeling proud)

352
00:12:14,430 --> 00:12:16,900
You said you've watched our show often.

353
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,270
Yes. I started watching it from the first season.

354
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:20,270
The episode with Cho Jung Seok.

355
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:21,270
(He's been keeping up with the show.)

356
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:23,070
- Right. - Wasn't it the start of your show?

357
00:12:23,070 --> 00:12:24,310
- It was the start of our show. - Yes, it was the beginning.

358
00:12:24,610 --> 00:12:26,980
I enjoyed the episode with the cast of "Nine Puzzles."

359
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:28,010
(The episode with Suk Ku and Da Mi)

360
00:12:28,010 --> 00:12:29,780
- Suk Ku and Da Mi. - Suk Ku and Da Mi. Yes.

361
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,610
You filmed that around here.

362
00:12:31,610 --> 00:12:32,780
- Right. - Yes.

363
00:12:32,780 --> 00:12:35,480
They were good at those games.

364
00:12:36,050 --> 00:12:37,190
Do you play games?

365
00:12:37,950 --> 00:12:39,560
I'm quite competitive.

366
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:40,760
Gosh. Usually,

367
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,690
- games don't turn out well. - They don't turn out well.

368
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:44,530
If he's only competitive...

369
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,060
Okay. I'll do a good job.

370
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:48,560
(The fan of the show is determined.)

371
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:50,100
What about you? Do you play games?

372
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:51,370
I'm also competitive.

373
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:53,970
So I don't play games.

374
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,540
(But we have to play games.)

375
00:12:55,540 --> 00:12:56,610
- I see. - I hate losing.

376
00:12:57,340 --> 00:12:58,810
- I hate losing. - Because you hate losing?

377
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:02,040
Wait. Then,

378
00:13:02,140 --> 00:13:03,780
we have to pay for our meal.

379
00:13:04,010 --> 00:13:05,580
Are there any games you play...

380
00:13:05,580 --> 00:13:07,420
to decide who pays for the meal?

381
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:08,920
- The ghost leg. - It's...

382
00:13:09,220 --> 00:13:10,620
- That's not a bad idea. - Gosh.

383
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,320
A class game for a change. Pick your spots.

384
00:13:12,490 --> 00:13:14,260
- I'll take whatever is left. - Okay.

385
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:16,160
- I'll go with number 1. - Sung Woong for number 1.

386
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:17,830
- I'll go with number 2. - Number 2.

387
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:20,630
- I'll go with number four. - Sounds good.

388
00:13:21,060 --> 00:13:23,300
Let's start with number one.

389
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:25,770
(Number 1, Sung Woong)

390
00:13:28,370 --> 00:13:31,670
(Chosen)

391
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:38,480
(Chosen)

392
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:39,620
(Sung Woong is exempted.)

393
00:13:39,620 --> 00:13:42,120
- My gosh. - Gosh, he was close.

394
00:13:42,180 --> 00:13:43,190
He managed to dodge it.

395
00:13:43,650 --> 00:13:44,990
- Number two. - Okay.

396
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:46,090
- That's Sang Yun's, right? - Yes.

397
00:13:46,390 --> 00:13:52,190
(Chosen)

398
00:13:52,190 --> 00:13:54,100
(Sang Yun is exempted.)

399
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:56,770
(A high-five)

400
00:13:57,370 --> 00:13:59,570
(That means it's between...)

401
00:13:59,570 --> 00:14:00,700
(Jae Suk and Yeon Seok.)

402
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:02,200
It's one of us, then.

403
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:04,370
- Let's see. - Let's go with Yeon Shik's.

404
00:14:04,370 --> 00:14:06,110
- My number was four. - Yeon Shik.

405
00:14:07,610 --> 00:14:11,010
(Chosen)

406
00:14:11,010 --> 00:14:12,150
It's going pretty far.

407
00:14:12,610 --> 00:14:16,450
(This leg will decide the outcome.)

408
00:14:18,820 --> 00:14:20,720
(Chosen)

409
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:24,560
(Yoo Yeon Seok is chosen to pay!)

410
00:14:24,890 --> 00:14:26,660
(He can't conceal his joy.)

411
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:31,370
- Thank you for the food. - Thanks for the food, Yeon Shik.

412
00:14:31,730 --> 00:14:32,770
Come on. Just pay.

413
00:14:33,070 --> 00:14:34,240
Thank you for the food, Yeon Shik.

414
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,540
- Sure. - Thank you for the food.

415
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:38,170
All right.

416
00:14:38,170 --> 00:14:39,780
Let's find out about today's Whenever Guests.

417
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,040
"Cho Kwang Jin."

418
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,580
"I'm like a permanent fixture."

419
00:14:43,580 --> 00:14:45,750
"I've been here in Daechi-dong for over 40 years."

420
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:48,650
"Every day, I'm building houses..."

421
00:14:48,850 --> 00:14:51,120
"with round stones."

422
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:54,060
"Come over to my black-and-white house."

423
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:56,430
- "I'll show you my flawless move." - That's great.

424
00:14:56,890 --> 00:14:58,460
Round stones? Go.

425
00:14:58,460 --> 00:14:59,660
- Yes, it's Go. - Yes.

426
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,260
Hey. Do you think we might play Alkkagi there?

427
00:15:02,260 --> 00:15:03,270
It must be Alkkagi.

428
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:04,670
(What kind of mission will they play?)

429
00:15:04,670 --> 00:15:05,670
Wait.

430
00:15:05,830 --> 00:15:07,800
- We don't have much time left. - Let's go.

431
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:10,610
- I'll pay. - No, we played a game for it.

432
00:15:10,610 --> 00:15:12,540
- It was just a game. - My gosh, no.

433
00:15:12,540 --> 00:15:14,140
- We played a game for it. Here. - Gosh.

434
00:15:14,140 --> 00:15:16,580
- He brought us to a good place. - Right.

435
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:18,650
I got to find out about uljjajang thanks to you.

436
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:20,350
- Okay. - Thank you.

437
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:22,280
- Thank you. - Thank you.

438
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,320
Thank you.

439
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:24,590
Thank you for the meal, Yeon Shik.

440
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:25,990
- Gosh. - Thank you.

441
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:27,620
The youngest in the group paid for the meal.

442
00:15:27,620 --> 00:15:28,790
(A heartwarming scene where the youngest buys)

443
00:15:28,790 --> 00:15:30,590
It's great to have a free meal from the youngest.

444
00:15:30,590 --> 00:15:32,030
(The older guys are feeling great.)

445
00:15:32,030 --> 00:15:33,060
Where are we? Where do we need to go?

446
00:15:33,060 --> 00:15:34,800
I told you. We're going to that complex.

447
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,200
- It's this way. - It's inside the complex?

448
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,200
- Yes. - I see.

449
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:39,440
- We can go this way or that way. - Yes.

450
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:41,100
- Well... - Let's go this way.

451
00:15:41,270 --> 00:15:43,540
- Yes. Let's take the main road. - That's the main road.

452
00:15:43,670 --> 00:15:46,210
We'll see Daechi Station then.

453
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:50,580
By the way, how did you and Jae Suk become friends?

454
00:15:50,580 --> 00:15:51,680
- We were in the same baseball club. - Well,

455
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,380
- we were in the same baseball club. - Really?

456
00:15:53,380 --> 00:15:54,480
And we're the same age.

457
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:56,520
I was on so many of his shows like "Happy Together."

458
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:57,690
(He was almost on all of Jae Suk's shows.)

459
00:15:57,690 --> 00:15:59,190
"Running Man."

460
00:15:59,890 --> 00:16:00,990
Wait, you play baseball?

461
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:02,620
Not anymore.

462
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:04,060
- I used to play back in the day. - Well,

463
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:06,200
I'm talking about the 90s.

464
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,600
- Mid-2000s. - Mid-2000s.

465
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:11,200
- Mid-2000s. - I used to play until mid-2000s.

466
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,440
- It's... - What position did you play?

467
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,740
- A center fielder. - A center fielder.

468
00:16:14,740 --> 00:16:15,800
You were a center fielder?

469
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,440
- He was a center fielder too. - Right.

470
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:20,810
So you guys weren't the main players.

471
00:16:20,940 --> 00:16:23,250
- Come on. - You weren't key players.

472
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,910
Center fielders are very important. Outfield defense is key.

473
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:28,080
Hey, center fielders are the most important outfielders.

474
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:29,820
- Right. - Hey, Jung Hoo...

475
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:31,820
is a center fielder in San Francisco.

476
00:16:32,050 --> 00:16:34,520
- Really? - We have to cover both sides.

477
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:36,630
But it could be different...

478
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:38,060
with amateur baseball clubs.

479
00:16:38,060 --> 00:16:39,960
Don't athletic people...

480
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,160
- Listen. - So you're trying to tell us...

481
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:42,970
- typically become pitchers? - Gosh.

482
00:16:42,970 --> 00:16:44,700
- I got it. - That's just my point.

483
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:46,600
- Hey, it's true that in MLB, - That little...

484
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,700
pitchers take up 70 percent.

485
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:48,740
- It's true, but... - Hey.

486
00:16:48,770 --> 00:16:50,910
You enjoyed his uljjajang. What on earth...

487
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:52,310
- are you saying? - Right.

488
00:16:52,310 --> 00:16:53,380
Do you play baseball?

489
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:54,840
I was also in an amateur baseball club.

490
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,510
I've been playing for 30 years.

491
00:16:56,510 --> 00:16:57,680
- You still play? - You still play?

492
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:59,650
I'm the captain of our team.

493
00:16:59,650 --> 00:17:01,120
- You're the captain. - You are?

494
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,450
I founded this team three years ago.

495
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:04,620
I don't play with Jun Ha anymore.

496
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:05,790
- You left his club? - A captain of a different team?

497
00:17:05,790 --> 00:17:06,960
I can't play with his club anymore.

498
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,020
I know it sounds like an excuse.

499
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:10,530
But it's not easy to play baseball...

500
00:17:11,290 --> 00:17:12,760
after getting married.

501
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:13,800
Right.

502
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,230
Do you play any sports, Sang Yun?

503
00:17:15,630 --> 00:17:16,970
- He plays basketball. - I like basketball.

504
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:18,570
- You play basketball? - Oh, right.

505
00:17:18,930 --> 00:17:21,640
He was on the variety show where Jang Hoon was a coach.

506
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,740
Was it a variety show?

507
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:24,070
- Yes. It was a long time. - You were on that, right?

508
00:17:24,070 --> 00:17:25,240
It was called "Handsome Tigers."

509
00:17:25,910 --> 00:17:27,240
You have to be handsome to join the team, right?

510
00:17:29,180 --> 00:17:30,680
Some of them weren't, actually.

511
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:31,710
But...

512
00:17:31,810 --> 00:17:33,280
the coach isn't handsome.

513
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:34,950
He was born in the Year of the Tiger,

514
00:17:34,950 --> 00:17:36,450
- I mean... - so we were the Tigers.

515
00:17:36,450 --> 00:17:37,450
- I see. - Yes.

516
00:17:37,450 --> 00:17:38,520
(The coach had the "tiger" part.)

517
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:39,760
What a clever way to dodge the question.

518
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:40,920
He had the "tiger" part.

519
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,490
- Yes. - He had the "tiger" part.

520
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,430
(Thinking)

521
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:47,260
I'm itching to share a dad joke now.

522
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,700
- What? - A tiger got a new car.

523
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:52,500
He was driving it.

524
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:53,800
He saw a lion then.

525
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,300
So he rolled down the window. Guess what he said to the lion.

526
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,410
(Sung Woong's 2nd dad joke)

527
00:17:56,410 --> 00:17:58,340
Gosh. Why does he know so many dad jokes?

528
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:00,610
After rolling down the window...

529
00:18:00,610 --> 00:18:02,910
(What did the tiger with a new car say?)

530
00:18:03,810 --> 00:18:05,350
- Tiger as in "Get in." - That's it.

531
00:18:05,350 --> 00:18:06,380
"Get in?"

532
00:18:06,650 --> 00:18:08,520
(Oh, no.)

533
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:09,550
"Get in?"

534
00:18:10,490 --> 00:18:11,620
I'm sorry, Yeon Seok.

535
00:18:12,020 --> 00:18:13,490
- That was a good one. - That was good.

536
00:18:13,490 --> 00:18:14,560
- That was good. - Hey.

537
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,260
- Where... - We can relate to you.

538
00:18:16,290 --> 00:18:17,760
Where did you hear this joke?

539
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:18,830
- Where did you find these jokes? - There's a book.

540
00:18:18,830 --> 00:18:20,700
It's "500 Dad Jokes."

541
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:22,930
- There's a book. - There are 500 jokes?

542
00:18:22,930 --> 00:18:24,430
It's called "500 Dad Jokes?"

543
00:18:24,430 --> 00:18:26,740
My son loves dad jokes to the point that...

544
00:18:26,740 --> 00:18:28,200
he wants to do a joke battle.

545
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,340
- A joke battle? - Yes.

546
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:31,470
So we tell each other jokes all the time.

547
00:18:31,870 --> 00:18:34,040
What's the city flower shop owners hate?

548
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:35,110
Sydney.

549
00:18:35,140 --> 00:18:36,280
- As in "Wither." - What's the city...

550
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,450
restaurant owners hate the most?

551
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:39,050
Shanghai. We tell jokes like this.

552
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:41,920
He asked, "What's a letter of apology in English?"

553
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,290
I said I didn't know. Then, he said, "Global."

554
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:44,290
(As in "being punished in writing")

555
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:46,090
- Right. Punished in writing. - "Global."

556
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:47,960
He keeps telling me these jokes.

557
00:18:48,390 --> 00:18:49,930
It's fun, though.

558
00:18:49,930 --> 00:18:52,560
It's getting more fun as we keep sharing the jokes.

559
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:55,100
- And dad jokes suit him well. - Right.

560
00:18:55,430 --> 00:18:58,730
- My son is 17 years old. - Right.

561
00:18:58,730 --> 00:19:01,100
He still gives a peck on my lips in the morning...

562
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:02,170
- when I leave for work. - Really?

563
00:19:02,170 --> 00:19:03,940
- Yes. - Your 17-year-old son...

564
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:04,970
still does that?

565
00:19:04,970 --> 00:19:06,540
- Gosh. - Of course. When he does that,

566
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:08,210
we both wipe our lips and pretend it's awful.

567
00:19:08,210 --> 00:19:09,240
(They pretend it's gross.)

568
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:11,250
- I'm grateful, though. He's 17. - Of course.

569
00:19:11,550 --> 00:19:12,550
Of course, you're grateful.

570
00:19:12,550 --> 00:19:14,750
That's when boys around his age stop talking to their parents.

571
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:16,080
Right. I'm grateful.

572
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,390
I can see that.

573
00:19:17,450 --> 00:19:18,920
- We're here. - Yes.

574
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:22,520
- We have to go to Building B. - B?

575
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:24,760
- My gosh, this place... - Seriously.

576
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,360
It's an old commercial complex.

577
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:27,660
- Right? - Yes.

578
00:19:28,030 --> 00:19:29,500
I rarely come to this neighborhood...

579
00:19:29,770 --> 00:19:31,230
because of the traffic jam.

580
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:34,440
- There's always traffic at 10pm. - Yes. There's always traffic here.

581
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:35,970
- Because of the cram schools? - There are...

582
00:19:35,970 --> 00:19:37,410
- a lot of cram schools here. - That's when cram schools end.

583
00:19:37,410 --> 00:19:39,370
- To pick up their kids? - All the parents come here.

584
00:19:39,740 --> 00:19:41,910
And there are delivery trucks too.

585
00:19:41,910 --> 00:19:43,850
That's why there are so many good restaurants here.

586
00:19:43,850 --> 00:19:45,480
A lot of people come and go in this neighborhood.

587
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:47,750
It's such a safe neighborhood.

588
00:19:48,150 --> 00:19:51,950
My son would be walking home late from this neighborhood.

589
00:19:51,950 --> 00:19:54,360
I don't have to worry about his safety. You know?

590
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:56,120
Exit Seven is over there.

591
00:19:56,330 --> 00:19:57,390
- There? - Yes.

592
00:19:57,830 --> 00:20:00,260
- That's Exit 6. There's Exit 5. - This is Exit 6.

593
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,000
You really do know this neighborhood well.

594
00:20:03,270 --> 00:20:04,700
Let's do a good job with the games.

595
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,300
I hope we can give...

596
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,600
- all three presents. - Let's give it a try.

597
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,900
- Right. - There are so many shops here.

598
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:10,610
- Unit 218. - It must be on the 2nd floor.

599
00:20:10,610 --> 00:20:12,110
- Unit 218. - This must be the place.

600
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:13,540
- It's right here. - "Go Class."

601
00:20:13,540 --> 00:20:15,210
This place does look really old-fashioned.

602
00:20:15,210 --> 00:20:17,050
- "Cho Kwang Jin." - This is the place.

603
00:20:17,710 --> 00:20:19,780
- Hello. - My gosh, come on in.

604
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:22,720
Oh, my. Even the door is from the old days.

605
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:24,320
I see.

606
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,150
- Nice to meet you. - Nice to meet you too.

607
00:20:26,150 --> 00:20:27,520
- Hi. - Hi.

608
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:29,320
- Kwang Jin? Nice to meet you. - Likewise.

609
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:31,030
- Nice to meet you too. - Hi.

610
00:20:31,090 --> 00:20:33,660
- This door brings back memories. - Gosh.

611
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,830
Doorknobs used to look like this.

612
00:20:35,830 --> 00:20:36,830
Even the windows...

613
00:20:36,830 --> 00:20:37,830
- are old-fashioned. - You're right.

614
00:20:37,830 --> 00:20:40,000
- The AC too. - The AC is...

615
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,670
about 30 to 35 years old.

616
00:20:41,670 --> 00:20:43,540
- Exactly. - Does it still work?

617
00:20:43,770 --> 00:20:46,040
It works perfectly.

618
00:20:47,010 --> 00:20:49,010
Goodness, really.

619
00:20:49,010 --> 00:20:50,450
(Shaped by the passage of time,)

620
00:20:50,610 --> 00:20:53,180
(the Go classroom is the first spare time.)

621
00:20:53,180 --> 00:20:54,750
This is a Go class for children.

622
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,850
- Yes, exclusively for children. - I see.

623
00:20:56,850 --> 00:20:58,220
(Go Class)

624
00:20:58,790 --> 00:21:01,220
How long have you been running this place?

625
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:04,890
It's been about 44 years now.

626
00:21:04,890 --> 00:21:07,060
Four decades have passed.

627
00:21:07,530 --> 00:21:08,530
In this very place?

628
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:11,330
Yes, I've been here forever.

629
00:21:11,330 --> 00:21:13,370
- Gosh. - Looking at the door...

630
00:21:13,370 --> 00:21:15,670
Looking at the door...

631
00:21:15,740 --> 00:21:18,640
- The windows are really old. - Those are from the 1980s.

632
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:22,180
Even the Go board looks quite old.

633
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:24,210
That's right. It's been shaved down multiple times.

634
00:21:24,210 --> 00:21:25,310
- This... - It has to be shaved...

635
00:21:25,310 --> 00:21:26,420
every ten years.

636
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:28,750
- It has to be shaved. - The thickness...

637
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:30,450
The thick Go board has been shaved down to this.

638
00:21:30,450 --> 00:21:33,320
It was thick before it was shaved down.

639
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:35,820
By the way, how did you start...

640
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:37,790
this Go class?

641
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:40,160
- When I was a child, - Yes?

642
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:43,230
my dad used to play Go with the elders.

643
00:21:43,230 --> 00:21:46,270
- Right. - I was about 5 or 6 years old...

644
00:21:46,270 --> 00:21:48,470
when I watched him over his shoulder...

645
00:21:48,470 --> 00:21:50,570
and started teaching myself at home.

646
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:52,410
- Really? - You taught yourself?

647
00:21:52,670 --> 00:21:54,840
He received the Best Leader Award.

648
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:55,840
I did.

649
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:57,780
(He received the Best Leader Award...)

650
00:21:57,780 --> 00:21:58,810
(after learning it by himself.)

651
00:21:58,810 --> 00:22:01,280
I feel bad for children these days.

652
00:22:01,650 --> 00:22:02,980
All they do is go to academies.

653
00:22:02,980 --> 00:22:05,320
- Right. - For the entrance exam.

654
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:07,790
I'm still running this class to show that...

655
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:09,190
studying isn't everything in life.

656
00:22:09,190 --> 00:22:12,960
(He's been teaching children for almost 50 years.)

657
00:22:13,460 --> 00:22:16,230
My grandfather used to play Go...

658
00:22:16,230 --> 00:22:18,700
and tried to teach me several times,

659
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:19,970
but he failed.

660
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:22,400
If you had learned from me,

661
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:25,310
you would've succeeded 99.9 percent.

662
00:22:25,970 --> 00:22:27,010
- Yes. - Of course.

663
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:29,010
Let's play a game, sir.

664
00:22:29,540 --> 00:22:31,710
- A game of Gomoku? - No, Go.

665
00:22:31,710 --> 00:22:32,780
- Go? - Yes.

666
00:22:33,980 --> 00:22:34,980
His expression is like,

667
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:36,180
- "Why here?" - Exactly.

668
00:22:36,180 --> 00:22:38,790
Start like this, and you'd have a weak foundation.

669
00:22:39,190 --> 00:22:41,060
(Taking it back in a rush)

670
00:22:41,390 --> 00:22:43,690
Is it easy to get attacked from all sides from here?

671
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:45,030
That's right.

672
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:47,830
But wouldn't you be taken aback if the opponent placed it here?

673
00:22:48,030 --> 00:22:49,660
That's how children play.

674
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:51,600
- Sorry? - That's how children play.

675
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:53,340
You're as bad as a child.

676
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:55,540
So I teach children not to play like that.

677
00:22:55,540 --> 00:22:56,970
He makes some sharp remarks.

678
00:22:59,070 --> 00:23:00,840
- If you're bad at Go, - Yes?

679
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:02,610
just dig into some snacks.

680
00:23:02,610 --> 00:23:03,750
(Gifting snacks to Jae Suk)

681
00:23:03,750 --> 00:23:05,110
Are there snacks? Oh, gosh.

682
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,480
(A box of snacks for the children)

683
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:08,650
- Goodness. - There are many bits and bobs,

684
00:23:08,650 --> 00:23:11,050
- Right? Even these. - including snacks.

685
00:23:11,050 --> 00:23:14,120
I don't have anything to give the children as a souvenir.

686
00:23:14,190 --> 00:23:16,190
- I made these. - Are those all four-leaf clovers?

687
00:23:16,190 --> 00:23:17,830
- Those are all... - What?

688
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:19,230
I picked them all morning and evening.

689
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:21,400
- All of these? - Hold on a second.

690
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,000
So you picked four-leaf clovers.

691
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,700
- Even the sizes are... - These are...

692
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:28,570
- With so many... - This leaf is huge.

693
00:23:28,970 --> 00:23:30,310
- Wait. - It's huge.

694
00:23:30,310 --> 00:23:32,270
- These are... - This is extra large.

695
00:23:32,270 --> 00:23:34,280
(Such a large four-leaf clover is a first.)

696
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:35,610
This is quite a collection...

697
00:23:35,610 --> 00:23:37,110
- of four-leaf clovers. - For real.

698
00:23:37,250 --> 00:23:40,120
I give out four-leaf clovers in hopes they'll bring luck.

699
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:42,380
Do you go looking for four-leaf clovers?

700
00:23:42,580 --> 00:23:44,520
I do whenever I have spare time.

701
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:47,090
You look for four-leaf clovers...

702
00:23:47,090 --> 00:23:48,420
- in your spare time? - That's right.

703
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:50,560
On my way here,

704
00:23:50,560 --> 00:23:53,860
I pick four-leaf clovers along the Yangjae Stream.

705
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,170
I should look for some whenever I take a walk.

706
00:23:57,530 --> 00:23:59,030
- I'll be on the lookout. - Right.

707
00:23:59,030 --> 00:24:01,070
- You might even bump into him. - I might.

708
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,940
- Along the Yangjae Stream, - Yes?

709
00:24:02,940 --> 00:24:04,240
many elders...

710
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,540
- around Mr. Cho's age... - Yes?

711
00:24:05,540 --> 00:24:09,080
are doing something in the grass.

712
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:12,610
I go to Yangjae Stream for walks and such.

713
00:24:12,610 --> 00:24:15,150
- Across the stream... - It's probably me.

714
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,590
You two could've...

715
00:24:16,590 --> 00:24:17,650
- bumped into each other. - Right.

716
00:24:18,090 --> 00:24:21,020
What made you send a letter to our show?

717
00:24:21,020 --> 00:24:23,560
I didn't send the letter.

718
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:26,090
- My youngest daughter did. - Did she?

719
00:24:26,190 --> 00:24:29,900
I'm not a big fan of appearing on TV.

720
00:24:30,770 --> 00:24:33,840
It's because I can't really hear very well.

721
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:35,270
What?

722
00:24:35,270 --> 00:24:37,040
- He's wearing a hearing aid. - Yes, I'm wearing one.

723
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,310
- That's right. - I see.

724
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:43,080
And for ten years, I barely spoke...

725
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:44,850
for fear of making a tongue slip.

726
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:48,550
I turn down TV offers because I might say something I shouldn't.

727
00:24:49,020 --> 00:24:50,190
My youngest daughter's name...

728
00:24:50,190 --> 00:24:51,550
- is Ha Neul. - Ha Neul.

729
00:24:51,550 --> 00:24:54,560
She said, "You've worked for years."

730
00:24:55,290 --> 00:24:58,190
"The only way to remember it is by appearing on TV."

731
00:24:58,190 --> 00:25:00,160
So I told her to send you a letter.

732
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:02,030
- Is that how? - Yes.

733
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,470
So your daughter sent it to us.

734
00:25:03,470 --> 00:25:06,000
I'm grateful to my daughter as well.

735
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,670
Is this your family photo?

736
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:11,310
That's right. This is my youngest daughter.

737
00:25:11,310 --> 00:25:12,810
- Ha Neul? - Yes.

738
00:25:13,010 --> 00:25:14,940
- Do you have four daughters? - No.

739
00:25:14,940 --> 00:25:16,510
- No? - These three were my students.

740
00:25:16,510 --> 00:25:17,850
Students.

741
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:19,210
She's famous.

742
00:25:19,610 --> 00:25:20,980
- Guess who she is. - Who is she?

743
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:22,520
Who is she?

744
00:25:22,850 --> 00:25:24,520
- Pak Se Ri. - What?

745
00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:27,890
Her name is Pak Se Ri. She has the same name.

746
00:25:27,890 --> 00:25:29,660
Why do people get the wrong idea?

747
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:33,460
We were genuinely surprised,

748
00:25:33,460 --> 00:25:34,960
thinking it was actually Pak Se Ri.

749
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:37,330
We even had a student named Lee Kun Hee.

750
00:25:37,330 --> 00:25:39,100
- The name? - Yes, the name.

751
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:40,740
- My student's name. - Someone with the same name.

752
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:42,670
We also had Chung Yong Jin.

753
00:25:43,710 --> 00:25:44,840
It's...

754
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:46,540
Even the rich come to my class.

755
00:25:46,980 --> 00:25:48,240
Were there no Yoo Jae Suk?

756
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:50,650
Unfortunately, no.

757
00:25:51,510 --> 00:25:53,050
- Wait. - The name Yoo Jae Suk...

758
00:25:53,050 --> 00:25:55,850
That's not something unfortunate, is it, sir?

759
00:25:55,850 --> 00:25:57,550
- But you came in person. - Right.

760
00:25:57,550 --> 00:25:58,990
- I did. - Yes.

761
00:25:59,020 --> 00:26:02,220
We should see how many bonus coupons we can get.

762
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:03,960
Mr. Cho can take part...

763
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:06,700
in the game using a bonus coupon.

764
00:26:06,700 --> 00:26:09,500
- Give it a go, Sung Woong. - Go ahead, Sung Woong.

765
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:10,930
Cast a "Babamba" spell.

766
00:26:11,170 --> 00:26:12,770
Babamba.

767
00:26:12,770 --> 00:26:16,600
(Giving it good luck by calling out his favorite ice cream)

768
00:26:16,740 --> 00:26:18,940
- That's more than enough. One. - One bonus coupon.

769
00:26:18,940 --> 00:26:20,840
Mr. Cho can participate once.

770
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:22,110
Okay, which one?

771
00:26:22,310 --> 00:26:24,080
- Starting from Round 1 prize. - Round 1?

772
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,580
Why am I getting nervous?

