Like the earlier one.

1296
00:45:10,761 --> 00:45:12,661
It could bounce off like this.

1297
00:45:12,891 --> 00:45:14,231
Why don't you hit it this way?

1298
00:45:14,231 --> 00:45:15,261
Yes.

1299
00:45:15,631 --> 00:45:18,001
- You should take this one... - Don't let it go outside.

1300
00:45:18,001 --> 00:45:19,271
- Make it go in. - Okay.

1301
00:45:21,741 --> 00:45:23,301
- That's good. - You did it.

1302
00:45:24,101 --> 00:45:25,241
No, it's pretty...

1303
00:45:25,241 --> 00:45:26,341
(At least the black stone is inside.)

1304
00:45:26,911 --> 00:45:28,211
- What do I do? - Then...

1305
00:45:28,211 --> 00:45:30,341
We should take this one out first, and this one next.

1306
00:45:30,741 --> 00:45:32,251
- It'll be... - Right.

1307
00:45:32,251 --> 00:45:33,851
too difficult to hit it this way.

1308
00:45:33,851 --> 00:45:34,951
- Yeon Seok. - So...

1309
00:45:34,951 --> 00:45:36,021
- You... - Yes.

1310
00:45:36,021 --> 00:45:37,581
need to knock this one off.

1311
00:45:37,581 --> 00:45:38,751
- All right. - You know?

1312
00:45:38,891 --> 00:45:39,991
- Let's give it a try. - Be bold.

1313
00:45:39,991 --> 00:45:42,061
- Don't let go of hope yet. - Right.

1314
00:45:42,161 --> 00:45:43,891
- You can do this. - Let's be bold.

1315
00:45:47,391 --> 00:45:48,531
Failed.

1316
00:45:48,531 --> 00:45:51,931
(Try number nine is a failure.)

1317
00:45:54,771 --> 00:45:55,801
Round Two...

1318
00:45:55,801 --> 00:45:57,801
We're dragging Round Two for this long?

1319
00:45:58,741 --> 00:46:00,471
Gosh, this is our last try.

1320
00:46:00,771 --> 00:46:01,941
- It is. - This is bad.

1321
00:46:02,311 --> 00:46:03,841
We had a lot of chances, but...

1322
00:46:03,841 --> 00:46:05,581
We've been doing Round 2 for 10 times now.

1323
00:46:05,581 --> 00:46:07,851
(We need to give him the medical checkup voucher.)

1324
00:46:07,851 --> 00:46:10,021
- Last try. - For the last time,

1325
00:46:10,021 --> 00:46:12,091
- let's do a chant. - Okay.

1326
00:46:12,091 --> 00:46:13,691
- Sir. - We'll make sure to...

1327
00:46:13,691 --> 00:46:15,291
All right, it's for the checkup. In 1, 2, 3.

1328
00:46:15,291 --> 00:46:16,361
- Let's go! - Let's go!

1329
00:46:16,361 --> 00:46:17,721
(We're going to make it!)

1330
00:46:17,721 --> 00:46:19,491
- Sung Woong, try going last. - Yes, go last.

1331
00:46:19,491 --> 00:46:20,991
- Fine, I'll go last. - Yes, go last.

1332
00:46:20,991 --> 00:46:22,231
I'll try going first.

1333
00:46:22,231 --> 00:46:23,401
- Okay. - Sure.

1334
00:46:23,401 --> 00:46:24,771
- Practice. - One, two, and three?

1335
00:46:24,771 --> 00:46:26,571
- Right now. - Yes, practice.

1336
00:46:27,371 --> 00:46:29,371
- There you go! - Great.

1337
00:46:31,241 --> 00:46:32,371
- That's good. - Are we going?

1338
00:46:32,471 --> 00:46:33,811
Let's do it. In 1, 2, 3.

1339
00:46:33,811 --> 00:46:35,341
- Here we go! - Here we go!

1340
00:46:35,341 --> 00:46:38,981
(Out of 10 total tries, they're on the last try.)

1341
00:46:38,981 --> 00:46:40,051
We have to make it.

1342
00:46:43,281 --> 00:46:44,381
Good.

1343
00:46:44,751 --> 00:46:45,891
Good.

1344
00:46:46,051 --> 00:46:47,621
- Perfect. - My turn.

1345
00:46:47,691 --> 00:46:48,861
I'll knock it out.

1346
00:46:48,861 --> 00:46:50,221
- Yes. - Knock it out.

1347
00:46:50,221 --> 00:46:52,461
(Last try, Yeon Seok)

1348
00:46:57,761 --> 00:46:58,931
- Okay. - Oh, man.

1349
00:47:00,971 --> 00:47:03,271
(The black stone stopped before touching his hand.)

1350
00:47:03,341 --> 00:47:04,601
Oh, dear.

1351
00:47:04,601 --> 00:47:06,241
- It didn't touch me. - Let's go.

1352
00:47:06,241 --> 00:47:07,971
- Come on. - It didn't.

1353
00:47:07,971 --> 00:47:09,281
There was a backspin.

1354
00:47:09,481 --> 00:47:10,541
Backspin?

1355
00:47:11,281 --> 00:47:12,281
(Yeon Seok succeeds.)

1356
00:47:12,281 --> 00:47:13,381
Come on.

1357
00:47:13,451 --> 00:47:15,451
- Right here? - Yes.

1358
00:47:15,451 --> 00:47:16,651
Sang Yun, put it right there.

1359
00:47:17,081 --> 00:47:18,421
- Maybe this way. - Yes.

1360
00:47:18,621 --> 00:47:20,251
You have to hit it harder than you think.

1361
00:47:21,461 --> 00:47:22,861
- Right? - Not too hard, though.

1362
00:47:22,861 --> 00:47:25,161
- A moderate force. - Somewhere between those two.

1363
00:47:25,931 --> 00:47:27,691
Between "harder than you think" and "not too hard."

1364
00:47:27,691 --> 00:47:28,861
Then,

1365
00:47:29,261 --> 00:47:30,501
aim at the stone.

1366
00:47:30,501 --> 00:47:32,131
- Should I? - Yes, that way...

1367
00:47:32,131 --> 00:47:33,331
- It'll hit the stone. - Yes.

1368
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:35,001
But not too hard.

1369
00:47:35,001 --> 00:47:36,001
(Last try, Sang Yun)

1370
00:47:40,771 --> 00:47:43,681
(Don't go off the board!)

1371
00:47:46,451 --> 00:47:48,721
(The black stone is safe!)

1372
00:47:49,281 --> 00:47:50,281
You just...

1373
00:47:50,981 --> 00:47:51,991
Sung Woong!

1374
00:47:52,221 --> 00:47:54,691
There. That's good, right?

1375
00:47:54,691 --> 00:47:56,491
- You just tap it. - This is...

1376
00:47:56,491 --> 00:47:57,761
(Last try, Sung Woong)

1377
00:47:58,331 --> 00:47:59,491
(Gasping)

1378
00:47:59,961 --> 00:48:02,501
(The last one's heart is about to stop.)

1379
00:48:02,501 --> 00:48:03,831
(His hand trembles.)

1380
00:48:04,461 --> 00:48:05,831
It goes up if you hit it this way.

1381
00:48:05,831 --> 00:48:06,971
(Panicking)

1382
00:48:08,171 --> 00:48:11,301
- At least the medical checkup. - Yes, at least that.

1383
00:48:11,301 --> 00:48:12,311
(The last chance to succeed on their last try)

1384
00:48:16,581 --> 00:48:17,581
Failed.

1385
00:48:20,151 --> 00:48:22,981
(They fail for good.)

1386
00:48:28,591 --> 00:48:29,861
Why did I hit it at an angle?

1387
00:48:31,421 --> 00:48:33,731
No. I should have hit it straight.

1388
00:48:33,731 --> 00:48:35,061
I hit it...

1389
00:48:35,061 --> 00:48:36,661
I thought I'd save it this way.

1390
00:48:36,831 --> 00:48:38,501
- I'm sorry. - It was too hard.

1391
00:48:38,501 --> 00:48:39,531
It was.

1392
00:48:42,701 --> 00:48:44,071
Great work, everyone.

1393
00:48:44,911 --> 00:48:46,341
- Great work, everyone. - Sorry.

1394
00:48:48,741 --> 00:48:50,681
(They failed to give him the jacket and the checkup voucher.)

1395
00:48:50,681 --> 00:48:52,651
I guess it's just my luck.

1396
00:48:52,811 --> 00:48:53,881
You all played hard.

1397
00:48:54,981 --> 00:48:56,451
We couldn't bless you.

1398
00:48:56,451 --> 00:48:58,651
I'll give you gifts of blessing instead.

1399
00:48:58,651 --> 00:49:00,391
We can't accept that, sir.

1400
00:49:00,791 --> 00:49:02,291
We could never accept that.

1401
00:49:02,791 --> 00:49:04,561
There are four of them.

1402
00:49:05,091 --> 00:49:09,101
By the end of the year, I hope you win the Grand Award,

1403
00:49:09,861 --> 00:49:11,771
the Rookie Award, or the Popularity Award.

1404
00:49:12,071 --> 00:49:16,101
If not, I hope you at least get a table full of good food.

1405
00:49:16,641 --> 00:49:17,671
Five leaves.

1406
00:49:17,701 --> 00:49:19,471
This is a five-leaf clover.

1407
00:49:19,471 --> 00:49:20,511
(A five-leaf clover)

1408
00:49:21,241 --> 00:49:22,641
- It's very rare. - This is great.

1409
00:49:22,641 --> 00:49:23,811
- It looks good. - Yes.

1410
00:49:24,181 --> 00:49:25,311
Thank you.

1411
00:49:25,311 --> 00:49:27,811
(They came to give him luck, but instead got gifts.)

1412
00:49:28,111 --> 00:49:30,181
This is all part of the experience.

1413
00:49:30,921 --> 00:49:33,151
- Thank you. - We're so sorry.

1414
00:49:33,151 --> 00:49:35,691
At least, I got something to remember this day.

1415
00:49:36,591 --> 00:49:39,131
I had so much fun. Although they failed,

1416
00:49:39,791 --> 00:49:44,201
I hope the next person gets lucky.

1417
00:49:44,361 --> 00:49:45,771
I hope you succeed.

1418
00:49:46,001 --> 00:49:49,741
I wish you the best of luck, Whenever Possible!

1419
00:49:53,511 --> 00:49:59,411
(Daechi Station)

1420
00:49:59,411 --> 00:50:00,981
I can't believe we failed.

1421
00:50:01,621 --> 00:50:04,851
(A shocking failure)

1422
00:50:09,591 --> 00:50:10,661
I have nothing to say.

1423
00:50:11,391 --> 00:50:13,061
This is tragic. So, this is what it feels like.

1424
00:50:15,161 --> 00:50:17,761
At least, we ate beforehand.

1425
00:50:17,761 --> 00:50:18,801
Right.

1426
00:50:19,301 --> 00:50:21,841
Normally, we eat in this mood.

1427
00:50:23,071 --> 00:50:25,111
Let's shake off all this bad energy.

1428
00:50:25,111 --> 00:50:26,111
- Yes. - Yes.

1429
00:50:26,111 --> 00:50:28,241
Sung Woong is especially tense right now.

1430
00:50:28,341 --> 00:50:31,041
- What's next? - Let's look it up.

1431
00:50:31,851 --> 00:50:33,351
It's such a shame, though.

1432
00:50:33,351 --> 00:50:34,951
- I know. - It was so...

1433
00:50:34,951 --> 00:50:37,351
- We passed Round 1 in 1 go. - How come it's so hard?

1434
00:50:38,181 --> 00:50:41,121
Park Ju Hyeok and Chae Yun Geon.

1435
00:50:41,551 --> 00:50:44,291
"Our birthdays are only six days apart,"

1436
00:50:44,291 --> 00:50:47,031
"and we've been friends since we were zero years old."

1437
00:50:47,261 --> 00:50:49,801
"We like bicycles and ramyeon at convenience stores,"

1438
00:50:49,801 --> 00:50:51,161
"and we dislike studying."

1439
00:50:51,331 --> 00:50:53,171
"We have the exact same taste,"

1440
00:50:53,171 --> 00:50:54,971
"so we meet up every day, even on vacation."

1441
00:50:55,301 --> 00:50:56,701
"Though we have no siblings by blood,"

1442
00:50:56,701 --> 00:50:59,511
"we're happy to have each other, the true brothers."

1443
00:50:59,771 --> 00:51:02,411
"Hang out with us before we go to the academy."

1444
00:51:02,411 --> 00:51:04,941
- They're students. - They sound like students.

1445
00:51:05,651 --> 00:51:07,951
- I want to get out of here. - Let's get going.

1446
00:51:08,451 --> 00:51:09,681
I feel too bad to stay here.

1447
00:51:09,681 --> 00:51:10,921
- Gosh. - I feel terrible.

1448
00:51:11,581 --> 00:51:12,821
I feel too bad.

1449
00:51:17,761 --> 00:51:19,091
It feels especially cold today.

1450
00:51:19,091 --> 00:51:20,891
All we can do is sigh.

1451
00:51:21,591 --> 00:51:24,331
- It's especially cold today. - I thought it was such an easy one.

1452
00:51:24,331 --> 00:51:25,731
The wind is freezing.

1453
00:51:27,031 --> 00:51:29,141
It certainly has gotten colder than before.

1454
00:51:29,441 --> 00:51:30,571
The wind is intense.

1455
00:51:30,871 --> 00:51:32,011
I feel so dispirited.

1456
00:51:33,141 --> 00:51:34,541
(Thinking)

1457
00:51:34,541 --> 00:51:37,181
I haven't felt this defeated in so long.

1458
00:51:37,181 --> 00:51:38,241
(Coward Sung Woong is hurt.)

1459
00:51:38,241 --> 00:51:40,551
- I used to laugh so hard... - Seriously.

1460
00:51:40,551 --> 00:51:42,121
when I watched this show on TV.

1461
00:51:42,121 --> 00:51:45,191
But the show is too tense to laugh at.

1462
00:51:45,691 --> 00:51:47,221
You have to perform a show tonight.

1463
00:51:47,221 --> 00:51:48,421
Cheer up.

1464
00:51:49,461 --> 00:51:50,921
He looks so drained.

1465
00:51:50,921 --> 00:51:52,161
(Let's cheer up.)

1466
00:51:52,161 --> 00:51:54,931
We'll definitely succeed in the next one.

1467
00:51:55,031 --> 00:51:57,961
- Let's make sure to win next. - We will.

1468
00:51:58,801 --> 00:52:00,001
- Let's cheer up. - Yes.

1469
00:52:00,171 --> 00:52:01,871
- We need to cheer up. - We must.

1470
00:52:01,871 --> 00:52:03,001
Let's do it well this time.

1471
00:52:03,001 --> 00:52:04,771
- Let's stop sighing and cheer up. - Yes.

1472
00:52:04,771 --> 00:52:06,141
We'll make it this time.

1473
00:52:07,041 --> 00:52:08,741
(Waiting for the light to turn green)

1474
00:52:09,011 --> 00:52:11,181
(Vroom)

1475
00:52:12,481 --> 00:52:14,551
(Vroom)

1476
00:52:15,051 --> 00:52:16,621
We're too depressed.

1477
00:52:18,651 --> 00:52:21,491
- It was disappointing, wasn't it? - Yes.

1478
00:52:21,921 --> 00:52:23,291
We're too depressed.

1479
00:52:23,291 --> 00:52:26,261
Is it actually better to have lunch in between?

1480
00:52:26,261 --> 00:52:27,361
Yes.

1481
00:52:27,631 --> 00:52:29,501
We should have taken some time to refresh.

1482
00:52:30,261 --> 00:52:32,331
Our mood changes...

1483
00:52:32,331 --> 00:52:34,101
- when we eat delicious food. - That's true.

1484
00:52:34,831 --> 00:52:36,141
- What floor is it? - It's...

1485
00:52:36,141 --> 00:52:37,371
Wait, it's that white building.

1486
00:52:38,041 --> 00:52:39,441
- It's a study cafe. - The white one?

1487
00:52:39,441 --> 00:52:40,511
Yes.

1488
00:52:40,511 --> 00:52:41,741
- Right? - That must be it.

1489
00:52:41,741 --> 00:52:43,611
- Right. They're students. - The study cafe.

1490
00:52:43,711 --> 00:52:44,881
- On the 2nd floor? - On the 2nd floor.

1491
00:52:44,881 --> 00:52:47,851
(Into the 2nd-floor study cafe where they're waiting)

1492
00:52:47,851 --> 00:52:50,081
- Is it on our left? - What's this?

1493
00:52:50,151 --> 00:52:51,551
Ju Hyeok and Yun Geon?

1494
00:52:52,351 --> 00:52:53,921
- Ju Hyeok and... - Yun Geon.

1495
00:52:54,221 --> 00:52:55,261
Where?

1496
00:52:55,761 --> 00:52:56,991
Ju Hyeok and Yun Geon.

1497
00:52:56,991 --> 00:52:58,831
Wait, there are different rooms.

1498
00:52:58,931 --> 00:53:00,561
That room has its lights on. Isn't that it?

1499
00:53:00,561 --> 00:53:02,231
- It looks bright. - It looks like it.

1500
00:53:04,361 --> 00:53:07,231
Mr. Yoo Jae Suk was really handsome.

1501
00:53:07,371 --> 00:53:08,441
What are you talking about?

1502
00:53:10,001 --> 00:53:11,671
Ju Hyeok, get off your phone.

1503
00:53:12,711 --> 00:53:15,211
Get off your phone, Ju Hyeok.

1504
00:53:15,311 --> 00:53:16,481
Whatever.

1505
00:53:16,981 --> 00:53:18,281
(Yawning)

1506
00:53:18,281 --> 00:53:20,011
This must be it. I only see two kids.

1507
00:53:20,081 --> 00:53:21,651
Are you Ju Hyeok and Yun Geon?

1508
00:53:21,821 --> 00:53:23,551
- Yes. Hello. - Hi.

1509
00:53:24,581 --> 00:53:25,591
So cute.

1510
00:53:25,591 --> 00:53:27,991
- You probably couldn't focus... - Who's Yun Geon?

1511
00:53:27,991 --> 00:53:29,561
- because of this shooting. - I'm Yun Geon.

1512
00:53:29,561 --> 00:53:31,361
Were you forcing yourself to study?

1513
00:53:31,361 --> 00:53:32,861
- No. - No?

1514
00:53:33,391 --> 00:53:35,031
Are you two soulmates?

1515
00:53:35,201 --> 00:53:36,361
- Yes. - We are.

1516
00:53:36,361 --> 00:53:38,301
- So, you're in 7th grade? - We'll be in 8th grade now.

1517
00:53:38,301 --> 00:53:40,101
- Moving on to eighth grade? - Yes.

1518
00:53:40,231 --> 00:53:41,701
If this is a study cafe...

1519
00:53:41,701 --> 00:53:42,941
- Yun Geon. - Yes?

1520
00:53:42,941 --> 00:53:44,771
They had this in the study cafe.

1521
00:53:44,771 --> 00:53:45,841
- I got one. - Oh, yes.

1522
00:53:46,411 --> 00:53:47,441
- What? - What is that?

1523
00:53:47,441 --> 00:53:49,381
They had buckwheat tea, barley tea,

1524
00:53:49,611 --> 00:53:51,411
- and other stuff. - I see.

1525
00:53:52,111 --> 00:53:53,751
- You went and got one? - Just a cup.

1526
00:53:53,951 --> 00:53:55,351
They have these at study cafes.

1527
00:53:55,351 --> 00:53:57,081
It's nice to meet you two.

1528
00:53:57,181 --> 00:53:58,751
- Hi. - Hi.

1529
00:53:59,291 --> 00:54:02,091
Do you usually study here before going to the academy?

1530
00:54:02,091 --> 00:54:03,091
- Yes. - Yes.

1531
00:54:03,121 --> 00:54:06,491
We normally study here until 3pm.

1532
00:54:06,491 --> 00:54:08,601
- You're in middle school, right? - Yes.

1533
00:54:08,601 --> 00:54:11,561
You'll be getting pretty busy with your studies.

1534
00:54:11,701 --> 00:54:14,131
Did you have time to apply for this?

1535
00:54:14,571 --> 00:54:15,841
Who applied?

1536
00:54:16,001 --> 00:54:18,641
My mom did.

1537
00:54:18,641 --> 00:54:19,911
- Your mom? - Your mom?

1538
00:54:20,111 --> 00:54:22,011
- It wasn't his will. - Oh, really?

1539
00:54:22,481 --> 00:54:24,341
Is there no one who volunteered for this?

1540
00:54:25,141 --> 00:54:27,081
His daughter applied for it, and his mom applied for it.

1541
00:54:27,081 --> 00:54:28,751
- Right. - Right.

1542
00:54:28,751 --> 00:54:31,321
They're not even that glad to see us.

1543
00:54:31,821 --> 00:54:32,851
I know.

1544
00:54:32,851 --> 00:54:34,091
(Disappointed for some reason)

1545
00:54:34,151 --> 00:54:36,061
I didn't know I'd actually get picked.

1546
00:54:36,691 --> 00:54:38,931
I didn't think much of it, and I found out I won.

1547
00:54:41,261 --> 00:54:44,261
He applied for it, but I said I'd come too.

1548
00:54:45,061 --> 00:54:47,531
Ju Hyeok applied for it, and you wanted to join him.

1549
00:54:47,531 --> 00:54:48,771
I really wanted to see you.

1550
00:54:48,771 --> 00:54:50,441
- I see. - Really?

1551
00:54:50,541 --> 00:54:52,771
